WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:20.000
If a prompt depends on your real codebase, generic wording is not enough. RyFine can bring in README files, configs, and source files so the refinement reflects your project.

00:20.000 --> 00:45.000
Open Context to upload files, scan a local Git folder, or import a GitHub repository. RyFine filters out noise and lets you choose what gets sent.

00:45.000 --> 02:22.000
Import a small set of files, preview the snippets, and include only the ones that matter. Then run the same prompt twice: once without repo context and once with it.

02:22.000 --> 03:10.000
Use this for code reviews, implementation plans, docs updates, or migration prompts that need to match the repo you are actually working in.

03:10.000 --> 03:25.000
Try RyFine now and see how much stronger your prompts get with the right context attached.